<Link id="l00023" /><CodeLine lineNumber="23"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Specialized YAMLIO scalar type for representing a binary blob.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00024" /><CodeLine lineNumber="24"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00025" /><CodeLine lineNumber="25"><Highlight kind="comment">/// A typical use case would be to represent the content of a section in a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00026" /><CodeLine lineNumber="26"><Highlight kind="comment">/// binary file.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00027" /><CodeLine lineNumber="27"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This class has custom YAMLIO traits for convenient reading and writing.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00028" /><CodeLine lineNumber="28"><Highlight kind="comment">/// It renders as a string of hex digits in a YAML file.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00029" /><CodeLine lineNumber="29"><Highlight kind="comment">/// For example, it might render as &#96;DEADBEEFCAFEBABE&#96; (YAML does not</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00030" /><CodeLine lineNumber="30"><Highlight kind="comment">/// require the quotation marks, so for simplicity when outputting they are</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00031" /><CodeLine lineNumber="31"><Highlight kind="comment">/// omitted).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00032" /><CodeLine lineNumber="32"><Highlight kind="comment">/// When reading, any string whose content is an even number of hex digits</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00033" /><CodeLine lineNumber="33"><Highlight kind="comment">/// will be accepted.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00034" /><CodeLine lineNumber="34"><Highlight kind="comment">/// For example, all of the following are acceptable:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00035" /><CodeLine lineNumber="35"><Highlight kind="comment">/// &#96;DEADBEEF&#96;, &#96;&quot;DeADbEeF&quot;&#96;, &#96;&quot;\\x44EADBEEF&quot;&#96; (Note: &#39;\\x44&#39; == &#39;D&#39;)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00036" /><CodeLine lineNumber="36"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00037" /><CodeLine lineNumber="37"><Highlight kind="comment">/// A significant advantage of using this class is that it never allocates</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00038" /><CodeLine lineNumber="38"><Highlight kind="comment">/// temporary strings or buffers for any of its functionality.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00039" /><CodeLine lineNumber="39"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00040" /><CodeLine lineNumber="40"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Example:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00041" /><CodeLine lineNumber="41"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00042" /><CodeLine lineNumber="42"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The YAML mapping:</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00044" /><CodeLine lineNumber="44"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Foo: DEADBEEFCAFEBABE</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00045" /><CodeLine lineNumber="45"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\endcode</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00046" /><CodeLine lineNumber="46"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00047" /><CodeLine lineNumber="47"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Could be modeled in YAMLIO by the struct:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00048" /><CodeLine lineNumber="48"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\code</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00049" /><CodeLine lineNumber="49"><Highlight kind="comment">/// struct FooHolder &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00058" /><CodeLine lineNumber="58"><Highlight kind="comment">///   &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
